<span class="medium">
<h2>LIMS Developer's Manual - Database Batch Conversions/Modifications<br>
</h2>
<h3><span style="font-weight: bold;">Overview</span></h3>
<ul>
  <li>The bin/convert_DB.pl script provides various database batch
conversion/modifications functionalities.<br>
  </li>
</ul>
<h3>Details</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Functionalities supported:</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Batch conversion of tables from MyISAM to InnoDB.</li>
    <li>Batch creation of missing indices for FK fields.<br>
    </li>
    <li>Batch creation of MySQL foreign key constraints for FK fields
(also have the option of fixing the field definition of FK fields if
they don't match the field definition of the corresponding primary key
fields)</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Operations can be done to all tables in the database or a
comma-delimited list of tables specified.<br>
  </li>
</ul>
</span>